oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Pit-type farm pond
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Clement, William L., photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: H.J. Young, conservation technician, is shown with complete pit-type farm pond. The pond will furnish water for livestock and be stocked with bass and bluegill for family food and recreation. Located six miles south of Woodbury.

One in a series of photographs of agricultural activities in Cannon County, TN that were taken by W.L. Clement, District Conservationist for the U.S. Soil Conservation Service, and his assistants between the mid-1940s and mid-1970s.
